==English==
===Etymology===
[[end]] + [[-ian]]; from a passage in ''[[w:Gulliver's Travels|Gulliver's Travels]]'' in which an emperor, after cutting his finger after opening an egg at the large end, commands his subjects to open them at the small end; those who comply are called "Little-Endians", while those who rebel by opening their eggs at the large end are called "Big-Endians." You fucking geeks.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-notcomp}}

#{{computing}} Of a computer, storing [[multibyte]] numbers are stored with the [[most significant byte]] at a lower (''little-endian'') or greater (''big-endian'') [[address]].

